I’ll keep this read-only and constrain the pass to the cited peck/spec-kit sources plus executor-selection contracts.
The key distinction is emerging: peck bakes model cost into agent frontmatter, while spec-kit exposes executor/model knobs but defaults review to native Opus and treats small-model routing as dispatch/prompt-craft infrastructure.
### FINDINGS

[F-009-01] peck’s blocking reviewers are pinned to small OpenCode-Go models at low reasoning: acceptance uses `qwen3.6-plus` + `variant: low`, code review uses `glm-5.1` + `variant: low`; spec-kit deep-review defaults to native `opus`, not a cheap verifier. peck: `external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/acceptance-reviewer.md:10`, `external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/acceptance-reviewer.md:11`, `external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:10`, `external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:11`; spec-kit: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_confirm.yaml:69`, `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_confirm.yaml:74`.
GAP: real. spec-kit has executor knobs, but default review is Opus. `.opencode/commands/deep/start-review-loop.md:107`, `.opencode/commands/deep/start-review-loop.md:212`.
VERDICT: ADAPT. EFFORT: M. RISK: med. BLAST-RADIUS: deep-review setup docs/YAML defaults, not core reducer.

[F-009-02] peck puts rigor in the rubric: code-review blocks on score `>=4` and acceptance blocks on lint/tests plus per-task AC coverage; spec-kit already has severity/evidence rigor but not tied to cheap-model selection. peck: `external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:66`, `external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:68`, `external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/acceptance-reviewer.md:31`, `external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/acceptance-reviewer.md:42`; spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/references/review_core.md:20`, `.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/references/review_core.md:32`, `.claude/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:333`, `.claude/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:347`.
GAP: partial. Rubric exists; “cheap model because rubric carries rigor” does not. `.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/SKILL.md:282`, `.opencode/skills/sk-code-review/SKILL.md:286`.
VERDICT: ADAPT. EFFORT: M. RISK: med. BLAST-RADIUS: review prompt-pack + executor recommendation.

[F-009-03] spec-kit already has small-model dispatch infrastructure: cli-opencode defaults to low-cost DeepSeek high reasoning, and sk-prompt-models maintains active Qwen/GLM/MiniMax/MiMo executor profiles; this is plumbing, not a verification policy. spec-kit: `.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md:247`, `.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md:263`, `.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/SKILL.md:200`, `.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/SKILL.md:214`; peck: `external/peck-master/benchmarks/models.json:2`, `external/peck-master/benchmarks/models.json:7`, `external/peck-master/benchmarks/models.json:11`.
GAP: partial. “Run cheap review gates” is net-new as a default/recommended pattern; “can route small models” is already present. `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_confirm.yaml:850`, `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_confirm.yaml:866`.
VERDICT: ADAPT. EFFORT: S/M. RISK: med. BLAST-RADIUS: command docs + suggested executor presets.

[F-009-04] deep-review can already run cli-opencode and pass `--variant` from `reasoningEffort`, but it does not select Qwen/GLM/low by default and fanout’s cli-opencode fallback is a frontier Claude model. spec-kit: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_confirm.yaml:852`, `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_confirm.yaml:853`, `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_confirm.yaml:866`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:308`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:315`; peck: `external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:10`, `external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:11`.
GAP: real for cost-tier presets; none for raw executor capability. `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts:34`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts:39`.
VERDICT: ADAPT. EFFORT: S. RISK: med. BLAST-RADIUS: executor preset docs/config validation.

[F-009-05] failure mode: spec-kit review scope is broader than peck’s story reviewers, so low-reasoning cheap gates risk false PASS on cross-surface traceability/security issues. peck reviewers are narrow: acceptance checks story AC coverage and code-review excludes “right thing built”; spec-kit deep-review spans correctness, security, traceability, maintainability and requires traceability protocols. peck: `external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/acceptance-reviewer.md:36`, `external/peck-master/src/assets/agents/code-reviewer.md:28`; spec-kit: `.claude/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:322`, `.claude/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:327`, `.claude/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:436`, `.claude/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:453`.
GAP: real safety concern. Use cheap models only as bounded first-pass or parallel lineage, not sole release gate for broad/system/security surfaces. `.opencode/commands/deep/start-review-loop.md:116`, `.claude/skills/deep-review/SKILL.md:454`.
VERDICT: DEFER blanket default; ADAPT opt-in/benchmark-gated preset. EFFORT: M. RISK: high. BLAST-RADIUS: release-readiness policy.

